  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Protect the Health and Safety of IDPs and Hardship Cases through Emergency Shelter Responses</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project activities provide for the protection of the vulnerable internally displaced families who are living in inadequate shelters through the provision of safe temporary shelter solutions, and adequate NFIs. This includes to provide rental subsidies to 148 families of the IDPs (non-refugees) who have not been supported by UNDP or other humanitarian actors. The rental subsidies will be disbursed for IDPs renting a shelter and being at risk of losing tenancy due to not being in a position to afford their rent. Six months rental subsidies will be granted. In addition, the proposed intervention will support the targeted families to be more prepared for the summer weather conditions through the distribution of summer NFI kits.</narrative>
  </description>
